	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />To be quite honest, transcoding is the absolute <em>wrong</em> way to go for making video fit into existing SNES carts. Transcoding is a way to show existing, pre-made video. Eg it would be great for putting the opening FMV from Tales of Phantasia PSX into the SNES game, at a huge cost to file size.
<br />
<br />What you should be doing is hand drawing the video to get it designed for low color, lossless form, and then relying on things like sprites to simulate mouth movements and clouds, and scroll registers for panning.
<br />
<br />Take a look at the opening animation for Wonder Project J for a good example here :)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


